      • getKeywordNames

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getKeywordNames()
        Returns a list of the keyword names used by this iteration as found in the resulting stream definition. These keyword names are returned as the full path to the task and/or file and specific keyword. In essence, they are formatted with their stream location as a prefix.

        StreamName/TaskLocation/TaskName/FileName/KeywordName

        Returns:
        the List of keyword names

      • getKeywordValue

        public java.lang.Object getKeywordValue​(java.lang.String name)
        Returns the value of the keyword with the given name. This method returns the value in the data type that matches value text. For example the value 13 would be returned as an Integer, and the value 13. would be returned as a Double.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the keyword.
        Returns:
        the value in the data type that matches the value text.

      • getKeywordString

        public java.lang.String getKeywordString​(java.lang.String name)
        Returns the text value of the keyword with the given name. The name in this case contains the path location to the task, and the file name for the owner of the keyword. For example: /relpath/task1/output/keywordname
        Parameters:
        name - the unique path and name for a particular keyword.
        Returns:
        the value of the keyword as a String.
